@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Tri_it' where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 8
colours.

                             How to play?

  You play by clicking on the triangular shapes located between the
coloured tiles. This will make a triangular rotation (clockwise)
between the 3 surrounding tiles like this:

       A            C            B
             ->           ->            etc.
    C  *  B      B  *  A      A  *  C

(where A,B and C are the tiles and '*' is the shape where you click.)

BUT!

  Sometimes, when you click, the tile located under may move along
with the 3 others, so instead of a 3 tile rotation, 4 tiles will
rotate, as shown here:

       A            D            C

    D  *  B  ->  C  *  A  ->  B  *  D   etc.

       C            B            A

  If you click on the lowermost tiles, you would think that as there
are no lower tiles, only a normal 3-tile rotation would take place...

  Think again! Even when there are no tiles under the lowermost tiles,
the uppermost tile act as a 'lower tile' and may move, and the tile at
right will take its place at the uppermost position... in other words,
it will make the same 4-tile rotation previously explained.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS:

 -@{b}New Game@{ub}:                     Restarts the game (or Left Amiga + "N").

 -@{b}Mini Triangle...Big Triangle@{ub}: Selects between the Mini, Small, Medium
                                or Large game board.

